Implementation of ERAS in pancreaticoduodenectomy in an Australian tertiary centre.
The early implementation of the ERAS programme was safe although some obstacles were encountered. ERAS was beneficial in increasing the proportion of patients reaching the target length of stay without increasing readmission, reoperation, or morbidity. Our findings support the continued development of ERAS in PD in order to standardise care and improve patient recovery.
